text: Jacqueline 'Jackie' Dyson (born 1943), is a female former swimmer who competed for England. ==Swimming career== She represented England and won a silver medal in the 220 yards breaststroke at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. She was a 15 year-old pupil of Bonner Hill School when selected for the Games and swam for Kingston Ladies. ==References== Category:1943 births Category:English female swimmers Category:Swimmers at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in swimming Category:Commonwealth Games silver medallists for England Category:Living people
